1) Creating files using touch and vi 
2) creating directory using mkdir, changing directory cd
3) change owner to root: sudo -i
4) change owner to otheruser: su - tomcat(username)
5) Editors: vi, vim, nano
6) File permissions: chmod 755 filename or directoryname 
7) Creating the user: useradd 
8) Creating the group: groupadd
9) changing the owner and group : chown username:username filename.txt
10) installing the software is not allowed from other, have to use 
sudo before any command:

sudo yum install git/any other software

11) giving adming permissions to any user: visudo and add the user name 
12) to see the users: cat /etc/passwd
13) to see the groups: cat /etc/group






